Get Predictions in Tableau Calculated Fields
Decision Optimization (Beta)

It’s easy to get Einstein Discovery predictions in calculated fields. In Model Manager, select a prediction definition, generate a Tableau script, and copy it into a Tableau calculated field.

To embed Einstein Discovery predictions in Tableau calculated fields:

Log into Salesforce with a user account that has the Manage Einstein Discovery permission assigned to it.
Open CRM Analytics Studio.
Open Model Manager.
View a Prediction Definition.
Click the Advanced tab.
Choose Create Tableau Table Calculation.
Model Manager generates a script containing the ID of the prediction definition, columns used in the model, and corresponding source columns in Tableau.

Click Copy to Clipboard.
In your Tableau worksheet, paste the script into the Calculation Editor for the target calculated field.

Optionally, modify the script to include additional parameters:
maxMiddleValues: The number of top predictors to return in the response.
maxPrescriptions: The maximum number of improvements to return in the response.
showMultiClassProbabilities: Determines if probabilities are displayed.

Example scripts:
{
“modelOrPredictionDefinitionId”: “1ORB0000000HC3KOAW”,
“columns”: [“Postal_Code”, “City”, “Ship_Mode”, “Row_ID”, “Profit”, “Category”, “Sub_Category”, “Order_Date”, “Quantity”, “Ship_Date”, “Region”, “Sales”, “State”, “Segment”], 
“maxMiddleValues”: 3,
“maxPrescriptions”: 5,
“showMultiClassProbabilities”: false
}

SCRIPT_REAL(
'{ "modelOrPredictionDefinitionId": "1ORB0000000HC3KOAW",
"columns": ["Postal_Code", "City", "Ship_Mode", "Row_ID", "Profit", "Category", "Sub_Category", "Order_Date", 
     "Quantity", "Ship_Date", "Region", "Sales", "State", "Segment"],
"maxMiddleValues": 3,
"maxPrescriptions": 5,
"showMultiClassProbabilities": false }',
SUM([Postal Code]), ATTR([City]), ATTR([Ship Mode]), SUM([Row ID]), SUM([Profit]), ATTR([Category]), ATTR([Sub-Category]), 
     ATTR([Order Date]), SUM([Quantity]), ATTR([Ship Date]), ATTR([Region]), SUM([Sales]), ATTR([State]), ATTR([Segment])
)

When the script runs, it sends a prediction request to the prediction definition in Salesforce. Einstein Discovery returns the results to Tableau, where it appears in your worksheet or dashboard.
